 The basics
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You might be connecting to the &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet"&gt;Internet&lt;/a&gt;
from a &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_area_network"&gt;local network&lt;/a&gt;
or using an &lt;a href="https://ooni.org/support/glossary/#isp"&gt;Internet Service Provider&lt;/a&gt; (ISP).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Accessing OONI data</title><link>https://ooni.github.io/post/mining-ooni-data/</link><pubDate>Tue, 24 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ooni.github.io/post/mining-ooni-data/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This page has moved to: &lt;a href="https://docs.ooni.org/data/"&gt;https://docs.ooni.org/data/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>OONI Software Development Guidelines</title><link>https://ooni.github.io/post/ooni-software-development-guidelines/</link><pubDate>Sat, 23 Feb 2019 01:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://ooni.github.io/post/ooni-software-development-guidelines/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://ooni.github.io/post/ooni-software-development-guidelines/QuattroEngineer.png" alt=""&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The goal of this document is to explain and explicit some of the best practices relevant to software development that we follow at the Open Observatory of Network Interference (OONI).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By following these development guidelines we aim to produce &lt;strong&gt;higher quality code&lt;/strong&gt;, which contains &lt;strong&gt;less defects&lt;/strong&gt; and allows us to iterate more quickly &lt;strong&gt;delivering greater value&lt;/strong&gt; to our end &lt;strong&gt;users is a shorter amount of time&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
